#Text=Lineup coming together for Manchester United charity match
#Text=Tuesday , March 6 , 2007
#Text=Manchester United will be taking on eleven of the top players in Europe in a celebration match next Tuesday at Old Trafford , and the lineup for the European XI is coming together nicely .

#Text=The game is a UEFA-Manchester United collaboration created to commemorate not only the 50th anniversary of the signing of the Treaty of Rome , but also the 50th anniversary of Manchester United entering into European club competitions .
#Text=Funds raised in the match will go to support the Manchester United Foundation , which works with local charities as well as UNICEF to aid children in need .
#Text=Italian Marcello Lippi will be in charge of coaching the European XI side , and his assistant will be Andy Roxburgh .
#Text=Confirmed players have slowly been filing into the team , but with current Manchester United on-loan striker Henrik Larsson confirmed , the XI is now complete .
#Text=Players
#Text=Henrik Larsson :
#Text=Current Club : Manchester United ( loan)Age : 35Currently on loan to Manchester United from Helsingborg , Larsson has been in sharp form as of late .
#Text=This charity match will act as a farewell for the Swede , as he is due back in Sweeden to play for his home club after his loan contract expires on March the 12th .
#Text=David Beckham :
#Text=Current Club : Real MadridAge : 31The former Manchester star will be returning to Old Trafford to play against his former club .
#Text=Beckham has been playing strong for Real Madrid in recent weeks .
#Text=An injury will keep him out of Real 's next game in the Champions League , but if all goes well he will be back to match fitness for the March 13th charity match .
#Text=Update : Beckham has been removed from the squad due to his knee injury .
#Text=No replacement has yet been announced .

#Text=Update : It is confirmed that Beckham will not be participating in the March 13th charity match , but Beckham will still travel to Old Trafford and be announced onto the pitch in order to say goodbye to the fans .
#Text=Ronaldinho : Current Club : BarcelonaAge : 26 Winner of both European and World player of the year awards , Ronaldinho is arguably one of the best players in the world currently .
#Text=After nearly signing with United , the Brazilian has won 2 La Liga titles and the Champions League trophy with Spanish giants Barcelona .
#Text=Carles Puyol :
#Text=Current Club : BarcelonaAge : 28
#Text=Another player from Barcelona , Puyol is one of the best central defenders in Spain , he was the first of his position named to Lippi 's squad .
#Text=His shaggy hair makes him easy to pick out on the football pitch , but his dominance from the back lures much more attention .
#Text=Gianluca Zambrotta :
#Text=Current Club : BarcelonaAge : 30
#Text=A member of the Italian World Cup winning team , Zambrotta is equally comfortable on either defensive wing , or in the midfield .
#Text=He is also a Barcelona player , and joined the Spanish team after winning two Italian domestic championships with Juventus .
#Text=Zambrotta has history with coach Lippi , as he played on his Italian International side while Lippi was in command .
#Text=Lilian Thuram : Current Club : BarcelonaAge : 35
#Text=Thuram is most capped player on the French International team , and he was with the French side for their European and World Cup victories in 1998 and 2000 .
#Text=Thuram has also won domestic league trophies in 3 countries with Monaco , Parma , Juventus , and Barcelona , his current club .
#Text=Steven Gerrard :
#Text=Current Club : LiverpoolAge : 26Though Gerrard plays for one of Manchester United 's biggest rivals , Liverpool , he is an amazing football talent in the midfield .
#Text=Gerrard won the 2006 PFA Player of the Year award , and has won several other medals including the European Cup , 2 FA cups , two league cups , a UEFA cup , and a Super Cup .
#Text=Jamie Carragher :
#Text=Current Club : LiverpoolAge : 29

#Text=Another Liverpool player , Carragher is well known for his grit and determination in defence , and is sure to cause the United forwards some problems , like he did this past Sunday in a match between the two .
#Text=Juninho :
#Text=Current Club : Lyon
#Text=Age : 32
#Text=The second Brazilian player on the team , Juninho is well known for his free-kick prowess , and is regarded as one of the best in the world for that purpose .
#Text=Juninho has played at Lyon in France for all 5 of their consecutive league titles .
#Text=Eric Abidal :
#Text=Current Club : LyonAge : 27
#Text=The French International plays alongside Juninho at Lyon after moving there from Lille in 2004 .
#Text=He has won 2 league titles with the French giants , as well as a Champions Trophy , France 's equivalent to the FA Cup .
#Text=Gregory Coupet :
#Text=Current Club : LyonAge : 34
#Text=Coupet is the keeper named to the European XI side , and plays alongside Juninho and Abidal at Lyon .
#Text=He , like Juninho , has been with the club for all 5 of their consecutive league championships .
